<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=13890&amp;p=183230#p183230"><![CDATA[
For what it's worth, Nintendulator 0.975 appears to pass (which is good, because it means my NES 2.0 support is at least <em>partially</em> working). In theory, it should be able to handle up to 256KB of CHR RAM (since the PRG/CHR ROM/RAM buffers are all statically allocated in .bss), which is conveniently the maximum amount the MMC3 itself can handle.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Mon Nov 21, 2016 9:19 pm</p><hr />
